author: COMSOL
description: This model solves the Boltzmann equation in the two-term approximation for a mixture of nitrogen and oxygen representing a background gas of dry air. Electron transport coefficients and source terms are computed by suitable integration of the electron energy distribution function over electron impact cross sections. It is shown how to prepare the electron energy distribution function for export so that it can be used in the Plasma interface.
